Let me think about this problem carefully.

We need to find a probability distribution P over a vocabulary of size N = 150,000 such that:
- KL(P||U) = 10.0
- KL(U||P) = 10.0

where U is the uniform distribution, so U(i) = 1/N for all i.

Let me work through the math.

**Forward KL: KL(P||U)**
KL(P||U) = Σ_i P(i) * log(P(i) / U(i))
= Σ_i P(i) * log(P(i) * N)
= Σ_i P(i) * (log(P(i)) + log(N))
= Σ_i P(i) * log(P(i)) + log(N) * Σ_i P(i)
= Σ_i P(i) * log(P(i)) + log(N)
= -H(P) + log(N)

So KL(P||U) = log(N) - H(P) = 10.0

This means H(P) = log(N) - 10.0

**Backward KL: KL(U||P)**
KL(U||P) = Σ_i U(i) * log(U(i) / P(i))
= Σ_i (1/N) * log(1/(N*P(i)))
= Σ_i (1/N) * (-log(N) - log(P(i)))
= -log(N) - (1/N) * Σ_i log(P(i))

So KL(U||P) = -log(N) - (1/N) * Σ_i log(P(i)) = 10.0

This means (1/N) * Σ_i log(P(i)) = -log(N) - 10.0

Now, log(N) = log(150000) ≈ 11.9183 (natural log)

So:
- H(P) = log(N) - 10.0 ≈ 1.9183
- (1/N) * Σ_i log(P(i)) = -log(N) - 10.0 ≈ -21.9183

